<header>
	
		
		Read this sample answer to the last writing task and find the mistakes. There are 12. <br/>Click on them.
		
</header>
	
<section id="body">
	<img class="rightFloat" src="../media/AC_AW_012.jpg" mode="1" id="1001"  /><br/><ol id="questionList"></ol>
</section>
<section id="fb1">
	<p align="left">1<font face="verdana" size="13">. <font color="#0000ff"><b>where</b> it is seen...</font></font></p><p align="left">This pronoun refers to a place or places.<font color="#0000ff"></font></p>
</section>
<section id="fb2">
	<p align="left">2. in <font color="#0000ff"><b>spite</b> of</font></p><p align="left">'Despite' is not followed by 'of'.</p>
</section>
<section id="fb3">
	<p align="left">3. <font color="#0000ff"><b>which</b> may be ...</font></p><p align="left">This is a relative clause and it needs a relative pronoun.</p>
</section>
<section id="fb4">
	<p align="left">4. <font color="#0000ff"><b>Although</b></font></p><p align="left">'Despite' is followed by a noun or a gerund</p>
</section>
<section id="fb5">
	<p align="left">5. <font color="#0000ff"><b>which</b> ...</font></p><p align="left">'That' cannot be used in a non-defining clause like this one.</p>
</section>
<section id="fb6">
	<p align="left">6. <font color="#0000ff"><b>whose</b> ...</font></p><p align="left">This is a relative clause and it needs a relative pronoun.</p>
</section>
<section id="fb7">
	<p align="left">7. <font color="#0000ff"><b>despite</b> ...</font></p><p align="left">'Although' needs to be followed with a subject -  verb clause.</p>
</section>
<section id="fb8">
	<p align="left">8. <font color="#0000ff"><b>where</b></font></p><p align="left">This relative clause defines a place.</p>
</section>
<section id="fb9">
	<p align="left">9. <font color="#0000ff"><b>whose</b> ...</font></p><p align="left">This is a relative clause and it needs a relative pronoun. 'Their' is not a relative pronoun.</p>
</section>
<section id="fb10">
	<p align="left">10. <font color="#0000ff"><b>while</b> ... </font></p><p align="left">What's needed here is a connector which shows 'concession'. </p>
</section>
<section id="fb11">
	<p align="left">11. <font color="#0000ff"><b>which</b> it cause ...</font></p><p align="left">This is a relative clause and it needs a relative pronoun. 'What' is not a relative pronoun.</p>
</section>
<section id="fb12">
	<p align="left">12. <font color="#0000ff"><b>although </b></font></p><p align="left">'However' is not a conjunction. It can't be used to join two clauses together in this way.</p>
</section>
